Cosmetics.name: Alternate Appearance Pack
Cosmetics.description: 3 new outfits, one each for squadmates Garrus Vakarian, Jack, and Thane Krios
Cosmetics.stats: Jack straps on a black biker vest, low-slung jeans, and steel-toe boots made for starting riots. Garrus suits up in a new military-grade, blue-lit armor equipped with a dual-input communication headset.

Cosmetics.name: Headwear
Cosmetics.description: Items that can be equipped in the "Head" slot of the loadout screen.

Cosmetics.name: Skins
Cosmetics.description: Items that can be equipped in the "Skins" slot of the loadout screen, and change the default textures of Atlas and P-body.

Cosmetics.name: Clothes
Cosmetics.description: Dress characters however you please, with a default wardrobe located in their closets.

Cosmetics.name: Lowriders
Cosmetics.description: Dozens of new options to match your new Lowriders.

Cosmetics.name: Alternative Look for Yennefer
Cosmetics.description: Check out this entirely new look for the mighty sorceress Yennefer of Vengerberg!

DLC.name: Kasumi: Stolen Memory
DLC.description: Concerns the recovery of data of great importance to Kasumi Goto. Adds two missions, a squad member, a submachine gun, and other items.

DLC.name: Overlord
DLC.description: Concerns the events of an experimental virtual intelligence that has gone rogue. Adds five missions and other items.

DLC.name: Lair of the Shadow Broker
DLC.description: Concerns Liara T Soni and her history with an information dealer known as the Shadow Broker. Adds a mission and other items.

DLC.name: Arrival
DLC.description: Concerns the events of an imminent invasion of a highly advanced machine race of synthetic-organic starships. Adds a mission and other items.

DLC.name: Peer Review
DLC.description: Introduces Challenge modes for both single-player and co-op, a leaderboards system, and a mini-hub area reserved for additional co-op tracks.

DLC.name: Perpetual Testing Initiative
DLC.description: It introduces the concept of multiple alternate universes, simply shortened as "the multiverse."

DLC.name: Criminal Enterprise Starter Pack
DLC.description: The Criminal Enterprise Starter Pack is the fastest way for new Grand Theft Auto Online players to jumpstart their criminal empires. Do not purchase if you already own the Criminal Enterprise Starter Pack.

DLC.name: Shark Cash Cards
DLC.description: Cash is king in this town. Solve your money problem and help get what you want across Los Santos and Blaine County with the occasional purchase of cash packs for Grand Theft Auto Online.

DLC.name: Blood and Wine
DLC.description: Blood and Wine offers over 30 hours of adventure, where beauty clashes with horror, and love dances with deceit.

DLC.name: Hearts of Stone
DLC.description: Hearts of Stone packs over 10 hours of new adventures, introducing new characters, powerful monsters, unique romance and a brand new storyline shaped by your choices.

Engines.name: Unreal Engine 3
Engines.description: The Unreal Engine is a game engine developed by Epic Games, first showcased in the 1998 first-person shooter game Unreal.

Engines.name: Source
Engines.description: Source is a 3D video game engine developed by Valve Corporation.

Engines.name: Rockstar Advanced Game Engine
Engines.description: The Rockstar Advanced Game Engine (RAGE) is a proprietary game engine developed by RAGE Technology Group, a division of Rockstar Games Rockstar San Diego studio.

Engines.name: REDengine 3
Engines.description: REDengine is a game engine developed by CD Projekt Red. It was designed for CD Projekt Red nonlinear role-playing video games.

Games.description: Mass Effect 2 is an action role-playing video game developed by BioWare and published by Electronic Arts.

Like the original Portal (2007), players solve puzzles by placing portals and teleporting between them. Portal 2 adds features including tractor beams, lasers, light bridges, and paint-like gels that alter player movement or allow portals to be placed on any surface.
Grand Theft Auto V is an action-adventure video game developed by Rockstar North and published by Rockstar Games.
The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time is an action-adventure game developed and published by Nintendo for the Nintendo 64.
Games.english_name: The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time

Games.description: The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt is a 2015 action role-playing game developed and published by CD Projekt.
The Witcher 2: Assassins of Kings is a 2012 action role-playing game developed and published by CD Projekt.

Genres.description: The games emphasize real-time combat where the player has direct control over the characters as opposed to turn or menu-based combat
Action-adventure is a video game genre that combine core elements from both the action game and adventure game genres.
In a platformer the player controlled character must jump and climb between suspended platforms while avoiding obstacles.
A third-person shooter is a game structured around shooting,[1] and in which the player can see the avatar on-screen in a third-person view.

Main_Characters.name: Commander Shepard
Main_Characters.description: Lieutenant Commander Shepard is the human protagonist of Mass Effect, Mass Effect 2, and Mass Effect 3, whose gender, appearance, skills and pre-service history are all customizable and have an impact on the story.

Main_Characters.name: Chell
Main_Characters.description: Chell is the silent protagonist in the Portal video game series developed by Valve Corporation.

Main_Characters.name: GLaDOS
Main_Characters.description: GLaDOS (Genetic Lifeform and Disk Operating System) is the central core designed to control, guide, and oversee the Aperture Science computer-aided Enrichment Center.

Main_Characters.name: Trevor Philips
Main_Characters.description: Trevor Philips is a fictional character in Grand Theft Auto V, a video game in the Grand Theft Auto series made by Rockstar Games.

Main_Characters.name: Ganondorf
Main_Characters.description: Ganondorf Dragmire known as the King of Thieves, the Great King of Evil, the Emperor of the Dark Realm[1], or the Dark Lord, is the primary antagonist of the majority of games in the Legend of Zelda series.

Main_Characters.name: Link
Main_Characters.description: Link He is the everlasting hero of the setting, having appeared throughout the ages in a never ending line of incarnations.

Main_Characters.name: Princess Zelda
Main_Characters.description: Zelda, Princess of Hyrule, best known simply as Princess Zelda is the name for several female Hylians, usually members of the Royal Family of Hyrule, who often play an integral role in the series.

Main_Characters.name: Geralt of Rivia
Main_Characters.description: Geralt of Rivia is a fictional character, the protagonist of The Witcher series of short stories and novels by Polish writer Andrzej Sapkowski, as well as its adaptations, which include film, TV series, comic books and video games.

Main_Characters.name: Yennefer
Main_Characters.description: Yennefer, born on Belleteyn in 1173, was a sorceress who lived in Vengerberg, the capital city of Aedirn.

Main_Characters.name: Ciri
Main_Characters.description: Cirilla Fiona Elen Riannon (better known as Ciri), was born in 1253, and most likely during the Belleteyn holiday.

Main_Characters.name: Triss Merigold
Main_Characters.description: Triss Merigold of Maribor was a legendary Temerian sorceress of the 13th century.

Platforms.name: PlayStation 4
Platforms.description: The PlayStation 4 (PS4) is an eighth-generation home video game console developed by Sony Interactive Entertainment.

Platforms.name: Xbox One
Platforms.description: Xbox One is a line of eighth generation home video game consoles developed by Microsoft. Announced in May 2013, it is the successor to Xbox 360 and the third console in the Xbox family.

Platforms.name: Xbox 360
Platforms.description: The Xbox 360 is a home video game console developed by Microsoft. As the successor to the original Xbox, it is the second console in the Xbox series.

Platforms.name: PC
Platforms.description: A gaming computer or gaming rig is a personal computer designed for playing video games that normally require a lot of power.

Platforms.name: Nintendo 64
Platforms.description: The Nintendo 64, stylized as NINTENDO64 and abbreviated as N64, is Nintendo third home video game console for the international market.

Series.name: Mass Effect
Series.description: Mass Effect is a science-fiction action-role-playing third-person-shooter video-game series developed by the Canadian company BioWare and released for the Xbox 360, PlayStation 3, and Microsoft Windows, with the third instalment also released on the Wii U.

Series.name: Portal
Series.description: Portal is a series of first-person puzzle-platform video games developed by Valve Corporation.

Series.name: Grand Theft Auto
Series.description: Grand Theft Auto (GTA) is a long-running series of video games, published by Rockstar Games and developed by subsidiary companies.

Series.name: Zelda
Series.description: The Legend of Zelda is a fantasy action-adventure video game franchise created by Japanese game designers Shigeru Miyamoto and Takashi Tezuka.

Series.name: Witcher
Series.description: The Witcher by Polish writer Andrzej Sapkowski, is a fantasy series of short stories and novels about the witcher Geralt of Rivia.

Side_Characters.name: Triss Merigold
Side_Characters.description: Triss Merigold of Maribor was a legendary Temerian sorceress of the 13th century, she has many side quests.

Side_Characters.name: Wheatley
Side_Characters.description: Wheatley is a fictional artificial intelligence from the Portal franchise first introduced in the 2011 video game Portal 2.

Side_Characters.name: Impa
Side_Characters.description: Impa typically serves as a nursemaid and/or bodyguard to Princess Zelda and often offers guidance to Link.

Side_Characters.name: Sheik
Side_Characters.description: Sheik serves as Princess Zelda alter ego in the game; to escape Ganondorf capture, Zelda passes herself off as a male Sheikah known as Sheik.

Side_Characters.name: Keira Metz
Side_Characters.description: Keira Metz of Carreras was a sorceress and former advisor to King Foltest of Temeria, a role that had also been held by Triss Merigold and Fercart.

Weapons.description: The Coil Railgun is an experimental weapon featured in the Enhanced Version of Grand Theft Auto V.
Weapons.stats: Weapon class: Heavy Weapons, Weapon type: Rail Gun, Ammunition capacity: 20 rounds

Weapons.name: Gusenberg Sweeper
Weapons.description: It is based on the .45 ACP M1928A1 Thompson Submachine Gun (popularly known as the "Tommy Gun"), which is famous for its role in 1920s gangster culture and in the Second World War.
Weapons.stats: Weapon class: Machine Gun, Weapon type: Submachine gun, Ammunition capacity: 30 rounds (50 with extended clip)

Weapons.name: Ocarina of Time
Weapons.description: An instrument Link uses to play music.

Weapons.name: Master Sword
Weapons.description: The Master Sword is the final key to the sacred realm that holds the Triforce, and only the one worthy of the title of the Hero of Time can draw it.

Weapons.name: Griffin Silver Sword
Weapons.description: Griffin Silver Sword is a Diagram in the Witcher 3: Wild Hunt that can be crafted by a Blacksmith (Weapons) or Armorsmith (Armor).

Weapons.name: Aerondight
Weapons.description: Aerondight is a legendary sword that has appeard in all Witcher games. Now it has been added to The Witcher 3 as well, and it’s probably the best sword there is.

Workers.bio: Nadine is a considerate personal trainer who is obsessed with the murder of her friend Jasper, nine years ago.
Flora is a brave former gallery-commisioned artist who is obsessed with running.
He grew up in an upper class neighbourhood. He was raised in a happy family home with three loving parents.
He grew up in a working class neighbourhood. He was raised by his father, his mother having left when he was young.

Kevin has a best friend who is a personal trainer named Edgar Mackay. They have a very firey friendship. He also hangs around with a personal trainer called Kaden Banks. They enjoy ferret racing together.
She is a Dutch Hindu who defines herself as bisexual. She did not finish school. She is allergic to nickel.
Kevin is a British Christian who suffers from a severe phobia of butterflies.
Roger is a former cleaner at a studio with a serious addiction to chocolate.
Cuthbert is a 52-year-old trainee tradesperson who enjoys listening to music, glamping and meditation. He is bright and exciting, but can also be very standoffish and a bit unstable.
Physically, Carla is slightly overweight but otherwise in good shape. She is tall with brown skin, black hair and green eyes. She has a mole on the end of her nose.
Fred is a brave partner at a law firm who enjoys stealing candy from babies.
She is an 45-year-old Australian senior Jedi who who enjoys checking news stories against Snopes.
He grew up in an upper class neighbourhood. His parents separated when he was small, but remained friends and provided a happy, stable home.
She is currently single. Her most recent romance was with a kitchen assistant named Taren Redd Hamilton, who was the same age as her. They broke up because Taren wanted somebody more reliable.

Mathias Forest Parker is a 61-year-old with an unfortunate habit of bumping off the people around him. His first victim was his late wife, Tia Lorraine Dunn, who he killed because he thought she was flirting with other people. He has since killed two more people.
